Shakira wrote some parts of the new version, and co-produced the song. The song was released as the second single from Shakira&#039;s second English album Oral Fixation Vol. 2 in 2006. "Hips Don&#039;t Lie" became a global success, topping the charts in at least 55 countries. It became Shakira and Wyclef&#039;s first (and to date, only) number-one single in the U.S.. The song became one of the world&#039;s best-selling singles of all time and one of the hottest songs of summer 2006. In the UK, this was Wyclef&#039;s third number-one hit (after The Fugees&#039; "Killing Me Softly" and "Ready Or Not") and Shakira&#039;s first. In many other countries, it became Shakira&#039;s second number one, (following the massive success of "Whenever, Wherever") and her third number one single in other countries such as Australia and Netherlands (after "Underneath Your Clothes").
